      "id": "MJUe",
      "code_hash": "7487c05c02d7bf14c9819bac9ec50d37",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"annotating-from-a-steam-deck\">Annotating from a Steam Deck</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The Steam Deck makes a surprisingly nice annotation console. With <strong>Steam\nInput</strong> you can bind any button on the Deck \u2014 including the d-pad and the\nfour back-grip buttons \u2014 to an arbitrary keyboard key. Those keys arrive\nin the browser as ordinary <code>KeyboardEvent</code>s, which means two <code>wigglystuff</code>\nwidgets can pick them up without any extra glue:</span>\n<ul>\n<li><code>KeystrokeWidget</code> lets you <em>see</em> what key a given button emits \u2014 handy\n  while you're wiring up the Deck's button bindings.</li>\n<li><code>AnnotationWidget</code> lets you <em>act</em> on those keys through its\n  <code>keyboard_mapping</code> traitlet, driving an accept / fail / defer / previous\n  flow without touching the laptop's keyboard.</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The two widgets are independent \u2014 this notebook demos each in its own\nsection.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "vblA",
      "code_hash": "d84882c672f541ed265650ce2886a8f7",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"section-1-what-is-the-deck-sending\">Section 1 \u2014 What is the Deck sending?</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Bind a button on the Deck to a keyboard key in Steam Input, click the\npanel below to give it focus, then press the button. The widget reports\n<code>key</code>, <code>code</code>, and any modifiers \u2014 exactly what <code>KeyboardEvent</code> would\nshow for that key on a regular keyboard.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
